@labelleviemedspa is one of my most favorite places to get skin tightening. Why? 
 
They have one of the best radio frequency machines out there called Morpheus8 but it can be REALLY painful. The topical numbing cream they use is the best! I feel next to nothing. Where, at other places, I literally can’t do the procedure. 

Here’s what it does… 

It can improve the appearance of fine lines and wrinkles, tighten lax skin, smooth out rough or uneven skin texture, reduce pore size, treat hyperpigmentation and acne scarring, help fade stretch marks, and even reduce some fat, though not significantly enough that you’d have to worry about volume loss in your face. 

In addition, Morhpeus8 offers the best value for the money when it comes to getting dramatic results without invasive procedures that can cost 10x the price!

#Morpheus8 #SkinTightening #RadioFrequency #LaBellaVie

Saying goodbye to Hielke fan de Gareladen the majestic Friesian. 

This magnificent horse was such a beautiful part of my life. Starting in 2010, Hielke was the first horse I ever did a photo shoot with. He was such a good boy, putting up with all the big dresses, including a 30 foot train from a wedding gown. Nothing scared him and he was a gentle giant. 

Then again in 2021 he posed like the regal war horse that he was for the cover of a magazine. Hielke was such a good boy allowing me to climb all over him and ride him with these massive gowns. 

Thank you to his beautiful care taker and the one who loved him the most, Shari Mahaffey @friesiansm for sharing him with me and the world! (She is the beautiful redhead at the end of the video.) How apropos; the last picture is of them both riding off into the sunset. ♥️

We love you Hielke! 
.

This was my childhood; sometimes riding every day preparing for shows.

It’s what kept me sane. I felt like I was never good at anything as a kid even riding. I saw girls change their horses in for better horses that could compete at higher levels as they got better. (that’s very normal in the show 
horse world) I was too in love with my horse, and I could never say bye to him. 

But what I did learn was how to connect with a horse and ride without a saddle and reins! 

As I grew up and gained confidence, I became good at lot of things because life is worth living and living BIG!!! 

I wish that for you… Live big, live loud and live happy! 
@my_cavago
